
1. Save all files to your repository
2. Run the setup script:
   ```bash
   chmod +x setup.sh
   ./setup.sh
   ``
3. Push to GitHub:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "Complete setup: Tutorials, CI/CD, Interactive exercises, and GitHub Pages"
   git push origin main
   ``
4. Enable GitHub Pages:
   · Go to repository Settings → Pages
   · Source: main branch
   · Folder: / (root)
   · Theme: Choose "Minima" or custom
5. Configure repository settings:
   · Enable Issues, Discussions, Wiki
   · Set up branch protection rules
   · Add collaborators
   · Configure project boards

Quick Verification Commands

```bash
# Verify structure
find . -type f -name "*.md" | wc -l
find . -type f -name "*.yml" | wc -l
find . -type f -name "*.js" | wc -l

# Test interactive simulator
cd challenges/interactive
npm test

# Verify GitHub Actions syntax
gh workflow view ci.yml